content: TYPE Continent  NAME Amorthland  Who rules: Amorthland is part of Tetra Argent. The ruler is King of the Tetra Argent, Alfrick IV of Dinmire.  Why is it called that: “Tetra” refers to the 4 continents under the Realm of the King: Amorthland, Modek, Tinollia, and Tagal. Argent (aka silver) refers to the state religion, The Grey Gods. Amorthland is named after Amorth the Conqueror, who led a great migration of his people through this land some 400 years ago.  Motto: “Might, Harmony, Argent.”  Symbol: Four 3-pointed stars, all silver, sometimes stylized on top of a pale or yellow scroll, otherwise on a black background.  Political Structure: Monarchy with Republic/representative elements.  Strong central government with various support programs in place, mostly consisting of military power. Highly effective and structured military recruitment and training regime, so military loyalty is strong (especially for how spread out it is). It is sometimes possible for wealthy merchants to work their way into a title or Nobility, especially if they marry strategically.  Customs: Most cities and towns celebrate Harvest season with an extravagant city-wide party.  Values: - Conservative/Liberal: Leans Conservative - Individualistic & Collectivist: Both. People value their autonomy and dislike being told what to do, but know they serve others for a greater purpose than themselves (some of this is due to the influence of the Grey). - Power Distance: Medium. - Uncertainty Avoidance: Medium. - Orientation to Time: High. Highly human-populated, and humans are very aware of their own mortality, as they have short lives. - Gender Egalitarianism: Low. - Assertiveness: High. - Doing vs. Being Orientation: High Doing. - Humane Orientation: Medium. - Indulgence vs. Restraint: Leans Restraint.  Superstitions and views on magic: People use magic for daily life on the small scale if they are able.  Fashion: European analog.  Conflicts: Things have been uneasy for roughly the past 50 years between Argent and Ulkken, as Alfrick III attempted to invade Ulkken in order to “bring it into the fold”. Ulkken resisted the invasion. Residents of Niputu also resisted Alfrick III’s invasion, and are their own country. Argent tends to deny this, and has occasionally made invasion attempts. However, Alfrick IV is not as strong of a military leader as his father, and hasn’t been successful in ruling Niputu.  Major exports: Beer, Wheat, Hops, Cattle, Soldiers, Clerics  Basic History: When the King’s father Alfrick III was young, he led a military force across Amorthland, Modek, Tinollia, and Tagal to “Unite the Tetra” under one kingdom. He mostly succeeded. It has been 51 years since then. In the

places furthest from Amorthland’s capital city, Dinmire, there is less structure and governmental support. If there is no military support in any given area, cities rule themselves and often consider themselves independent from Argent.  Primary Humanoid Inhabitants: Humans, Dwarves, Half-Elves, Elves  Notable Wildlife: Dragons in the Northeast. Vampire bats are known to live in the Southern Mountain area. Mountain lions all along mountain range.  Religions: The Petty (75%), The Sun (17%), Grey Gods (4%)  Languages: Common, Dwarvish, Mordigok, Orc, Elvish, Tagalan
